{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.2",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 2 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:1",
      "text": "My son, if thou wilt receive the utterance of my commandment, and hide it with thee;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:2",
      "text": "thine ear shall hearken to wisdom; thou shalt also apply thine heart to understanding, and shalt apply it to the instruction of thy son.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:3",
      "text": "For if thou shalt call to wisdom, and utter thy voice for understanding;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:4",
      "text": "and if thou shalt seek it as silver, and search diligently for it as for treasures;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:5",
      "text": "then shalt thou understand the fear of the Lord, and find the knowledge of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:6",
      "text": "For the Lord gives wisdom; and from his presence come knowledge and understanding,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:7",
      "text": "and he treasures up salvation for them that walk uprightly: he will protect their way;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:8",
      "text": "that he may guard the righteous ways: and he will preserve the way of them that fear him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:9",
      "text": "Then shalt thou understand righteousness, and judgment; and shalt direct all thy course aright.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:10",
      "text": "For if wisdom shall come into thine understanding, and discernment shall seem pleasing to thy soul,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:11",
      "text": "good counsel shall guard thee, and holy understanding shall keep thee;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:12",
      "text": "to deliver thee from the evil way, and from the man that speaks nothing faithfully.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:13",
      "text": "Alas for those who forsake right paths, to walk in ways of darkness;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:14",
      "text": "who rejoice in evils, and delight in wicked perverseness;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:15",
      "text": "whose paths are crooked, and their courses winding;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:16",
      "text": "to remove thee far from the straight way, and to estrange thee from a righteous purpose. My son, let not evil counsel overtake thee,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:17",
      "text": "of her who has forsaken the instruction of her youth, and forgotten the covenant of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:18",
      "text": "For she has fixed her house near death, and guided her wheels near Hades with the giants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:19",
      "text": "None that go by her shall return, neither shall they take hold of right paths, for they are not apprehended of the years of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:20",
      "text": "For had they gone in good paths, they would have found the paths of righteousness easy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:21",
      "text": "For the upright shall dwell in the earth, and the holy shall be left behind in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.2.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:22",
      "text": "The paths of the ungodly shall perish out of the earth, and transgressors shall be driven away from it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
